addLayer

public void addLayer(Layer layer)
Add a new layer to the layer stack. Layers get drawn in the order they were added in, with the exception of Marker-, Text- and Polygon3Dlayers, which are drawn in 3D - this means their adding order doesn't matter.

Parameters:
layer - the layer to be added

removeLayer

public void removeLayer(Layer layer)
Removes the specified layer from the layer stack. This should generally not be necessary, usually setting the layer's visibility to false using Layer.setVisibility should suffice.

Parameters:
layer - the layer to be removed

setBaseLayer

public void setBaseLayer(Layer layer)
Sets the base layer. The base layer is the first layer that gets drawn, with the exceptions of Marker-, Text- and Polygon3DLayer, which will are drawn in 3D.

Parameters:
layer - the new base layer
